    "Integration over the three angles ϕ, θ ℓ and θ K * provides the q 2 spectrum:dΓ dq 2 = 1 4 6I s 1 (q 2) + 3I c 1 (q 2) -2I s 2 (q 2) -I c 2 (q 2),(52)further integration over the physical rangeq 2 ∈ [(m ℓ 1 + m ℓ 2) 2, (m B -m K *) 2]gives the decay width.The hadronic uncertainties can obscure the sensitivity to NP, therefore it is convenient to define observables in which such uncertainties to a large extent cancel out.",
